{
  "text": "Migration occurred along a relatively well-defined corridor (figure 1a) (see also [CITATION_1] ). The individual effect on longitudinal variation was small in all main regions, and also after averaging it (table 1 and figure 2a). A strong seasonal effect was present, however, in the Mediterranean and Sahara, reflecting the loop migration observed in this population [CITATION_2] . A significant interaction individual \u00c2 season at Sahara suggests that different individuals made different, repeatable loops. In contrast to space, dates differed significantly among individuals in all main regions (table 1 and figure 2b). Timing presented a seasonally distinct pattern with a larger within-individual variation in autumn than in spring (figure 1b,c).",
  "correct_citation": {
